SAN DIEGO COUNTY DIGEST: PALA 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Two women in separate cars died in a head-on collision Wednesday afternoon on 
Interstate 15, the California Highway Patrol said. 
</P>
<P>
LaVerne Stella Rhea, 64, was driving south at 4:35 p.m. on I-15, one-quarter 
mile south of Pala Road, when her left front tire blew out. She lost control of 
her car, which crossed the center divider into the northbound lanes, hitting 
60-year-old Rose Fraticelli Dehaven's car head-on. 
