<HEADLINE>
<P>
HIGH SCHOOL ROUNDUP; 
</P>
<P>
2 LATE GOALS HELP SIMI VALLEY GIRLS TO ESCAPE WITH WIN OVER ROYAL 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By MIKE GLAZE In other 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Simi Valley High, the top-ranked girls' soccer team in the Southern Section 4-A 
Division, scored two goals in the final four minutes to pull out a 2-0 Marmonte 
League victory over unranked Royal at Simi Valley on Thursday night. 
</P>
<P>
"I wasn't worried about losing," Simi Valley Coach Mark Johnson said. "I was 
worried about going into overtime." 
</P>
<P>
Royal Coach Kevin Corley said he was not dejected despite the loss. 
</P>
<P>
"What this shows me is that we can play with the No. 1 team," he said. "To keep 
it close for that long was an accomplishment for us." 
</P>
<P>
Royal sweeper Stevie Campbell touched the ball with her hand within the 
Highlanders' penalty area, setting up sophomore Amy Hunter's scoring penalty 
kick with four minutes remaining. 
</P>
<P>
A half-minute later, halfback Liz Albin scored from four yards on Michelle 
Light's head pass. 
</P>
<P>
The shutout was the 10th for Simi Valley (22-0-0 overall, 7-0-0 in league play) 
and the 38th career shutout for senior goalkeeper Kim Duran. 
</P>
<P>
Royal is 14-4-1, 3-2-1. MIKE GLAZE In other girls' soccer matches: Grant 6, 
Garfield 0 -- Grant recorded its eighth consecutive Northeastern League shutout 
as goalkeeper Elana Tuizer relied on a defense that did not allow a shot on 
goal. Grant (12-2, 8-0) jumped to a 3-0 halftime lead on three goals by Amanda 
Walzer, who has scored more than 80 goals during her high school career. Walzer 
moved to defense in the second half, and Anne Remmers, Valerie Pearce and Pam 
Williams scored for host Grant. Chaminade 3, Notre Dame 0 -- Chaminade goalie 
Kathy Regan earned her 12th shutout of the season in a San Fernando Valley 
League match at Chaminade. Chaminade (16-2-2, 3-1-1), ranked third in the 
Southern Section 2-A Division, led, 2-0, at halftime. Carla Coppa, Natalie Dill 
and Anne McDermott scored for Chaminade. Louisville 3, Crossroads 2 -- Erin 
Joyce scored the winning goal for visiting Louisville on a pass from Sonia 
Freeman with about five minutes left in the San Fernando Valley League 
match.two first-half goals for Louisville (9-5-2, 3-1-1). Crossroads is 0-4 in 
league play. El Camino Real 1, Granada Hills 0 -- Sophomore center Tatum 
Mahoney's left-footed 20-yard shot with five minutes left broke a scoreless 
deadlock in the West Valley League match at Granada Hills. Mahoney's unassisted 
goal improved the second-place Conquistadores' record to 9-2-1, 6-1-1 in league 
play. Granada Hills fell to 4-3-1 in league play. Junior goalkeeper Alex 
Tolleson, with the help of fullbacks Stephanie Hopkinson and Erica Mangum, 
recorded her seventh shutout. Thousand Oaks 2, Newbury Park 2 (OT) -- Thousand 
Oaks' Phronsie Franco sent the Marmonte League match into overtime by scoring 
her second goal of the match, on a direct penalty shot, midway through the 
second half. Sophomore goalie Allison Hagen had five saves for visiting 
Thousand Oaks (11-2-2, 4-1-2).BOYS' SOCCER Newbury Park 3, Thousand Oaks 1 -- 
Dave Feldman scored on an assist by Mike Betancourt to give Newbury Park a 1-0 
first-half lead in a Marmonte League match at Thousand Oaks. Newbury Park is 
12-6-1, 4-2-1; Thousand Oaks is 4-9-2, 0-7-1.BOYS' BASKETBALL Glendale Academy 
72, Alta-Pasadena Christian 18 (game forfeited in third quarter) -- 
Alta-Pasadena Christian walked off the court with 4 minutes 18 seconds left in 
the third quarter, reportedly because it was unhappy with the officiating. 
Alta-Pasadena Christian received two technicals early in the nonleague game at 
Glendale Academy for not entering two players in the score book. Alta-Pasadena 
Christian's walkout reportedly was precipitated by two technicals, one on an 
Alta-Pasadena Christian player and the other on a coach, that were called in 
the third quarter. Chris Lindstadt led Glendale Academy (9-3) with 27 points. 
Glendale Academy's Guy Nembhard and Brian Alexander scored 15 and 10 points. L. 
A. Lutheran 59, Pacific Christian 49 -- L. A. Lutheran scored 20 points in the 
fourth quarter in a Heritage League game at Pacific Christian.GIRLS' BASKETBALL 
Hart 73, Burroughs 37 -- Oregon-bound Sara Wilson scored 18 points and grabbed 
15 rebounds for Hart in a Foothill League game at Hart. Alemany 62, St. 
Genevieve 39 -- Alemany's Qina Shigematsu scored a career-high 18 points to 
pace first-place Alemany (14-6, 6-0) in a San Fernando Valley League game at 
St. Genevieve. Christina Muller scored 18 points to lead St. Genevieve. 
Michelle McCarthy added 11 points. Notre Dame 41, Chaminade 38 -- Chaminade 
scored nearly as many points in the fourth quarter, 18, as it scored in the 
first three quarters, 20, but it wasn't enough to win a San Fernando Valley 
League game at Chaminade. L. A. Baptist 56, Montclair Prep 29 -- L. A. Baptist 
leaped to a 13-1 advantage at home and cruised to its third consecutive Alpha 
League win. The Knights (9-4, 6-2) have won six of their past seven games. Simi 
Valley 53, Westlake 49 -- Visiting Simi Valley jumped to a 10-point half-time 
lead against Westlake, the No. 1 team in 4-AA, and held on for the Marmonte 
League victory.BOYS' WRESTLING El Camino Real 64, Birmingham 6 -- The 
Conquistadores flattened Birmingham in a Valley League meet at Birmingham. Ted 
Glider (138 pounds), Roy Steinbock (145) and Andy Hasson (154) all recorded 
victories by pins for El Camino Real. Ali Afshar (105), Chris Kuhlen (126), 
Richie Jin (132), Saul Emard (165) and Young Lee (175) also recorded wins. 
