<HEADLINE>
<P>
PEOPLE: UNISYS CHIEF TO RETIRE, WILL JOIN LAZARD FRERES 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
W. Michael Blumenthal, Unisys Corp. chairman and chief executive, will retire 
in April to join the investment banking firm Lazard Freres &amp; Co. as a 
limited partner, Unisys said Thursday. 
</P>
<P>
Blumenthal, 64, will remain chairman of the Unisys board, the company said. 
</P>
<P>
Meeting in Detroit, the company's board chose President James A. Unruh, 48, to 
assume the additional duties of chief executive after Blumenthal's retirement. 
</P>
<P>
"After almost two decades of managing major industrial companies and 10 years 
at Burroughs and Unisys, the time has come for my long-planned retirement," 
Blumenthal said in a statement. 
</P>
<P>
Blumenthal, who engineered Burroughs Corp.'s 1986 takeover of Sperry Corp. to 
form Unisys, was Treasury secretary in the Carter Administration. He indicated 
last year that he planned to retire shortly. 
</P>
<P>
At New York-based Lazard Freres, Blumenthal will serve as co-chairman of a new 
international investment group, his statement said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
