<HEADLINE>
<P>
MORNING REPORT: TV &amp; VIDEO 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By SHAUNA SNOW, Arts and entertainment reports from The Times, national and 
international news services and the nation's press. 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Jackson's Show to Debut in September: Jesse Jackson's syndicated talk show will 
premiere in Los Angeles on KCAL-TV Channel 9 next September, and the program's 
distributor has assured stations that the show will be delivered even if 
Jackson decides to run for mayor of Washington. 
</P>
<P>
Jackson "has given assurances" that he'll do the weekly, one-hour TV series, 
"Voices of America With Jesse Jackson," said Barry Stagg, a spokesman for 
Warner Bros. Domestic Television Distribution. The series, co-produced by 
composer Quincy Jones, has been picked by 82 stations covering 60% of the 
national audience, Stagg said. SHAUNA SNOW 
</P>
</TEXT>
