<HEADLINE>
<P>
MORNING REPORT: TV &amp; VIDEO 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By SHAUNA SNOW, Arts and entertainment reports from The Times, national and 
international news services and the nation's press. 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Donahue's Moore Interview Draws Crowds: More than 1,000 people lined up 
Wednesday morning in Flint, Mich., for tickets to Phil Donahue's Monday show, 
in which he will interview Michael Moore, maker of the General Motors Corp. 
documentary "Roger &amp; Me." The satirical documentary shows Moore trying 
unsuccessfully to interview GM Chairman Roger B. Smith on plant closings and 
layoffs in Flint. Police helped disperse a crowd of people who waited all night 
in hopes of seeing Donahue and Moore but were turned away when the 1,266 free 
tickets ran out. SHAUNA SNOW 
</P>
