<P>
DIGEST / LOCAL NEWS IN BRIEF: MAN SHOT TO DEATH IN N. HOLLYWOOD AMBUSH 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A North Hollywood man was shot to death ambush-style as he pulled out of his 
driveway Thursday, Los Angeles police reported. 
</P>
<P>
Francisco Noguera, 37, was pronounced dead at the scene of the 6:45 a.m. 
slaying in the 11600 block of Hamlin Street, Lt. Charles Massey said. 
</P>
<P>
Noguera, described by police as a day laborer, was in his pickup when one or 
two Latino men approached the truck and shot him several times, Massey said. 
</P>
<P>
The men may have fled in a blue car, Massey said. Authorities had not 
determined a motive for the slaying. 
</P>
<P>
"This does not appear to be gang-related," Massey said. "This man was 37 years 
old. He was not a gang person." 
</P>
