<TEXT>
<P>
Money Supply Mixed: The narrowest measure of the nation's money supply, M1, 
fell in the week ended Jan. 15, to a seasonally adjusted $791.1 billion from 
$794 billion the week before, the Federal Reserve Board reported. 
</P>
<P>
The Fed said the measure known as M2 rose to a seasonally adjusted $3,218.3 
billion from $3,216.1 billion a week earlier. M1 includes cash in circulation, 
deposits in checking accounts and non-bank travelers checks. M2 is M1 plus 
accounts such as savings deposits and money market mutual funds. 
</P>
</TEXT>
