<TEXT>
<P>
Program Pays Death Benefits to Terminally Ill: Prudential Insurance Co. of 
America's new plan allows terminally ill policyholders and those permanently 
confined to nursing homes to tap into death benefits while they are still 
alive. 
</P>
<P>
Prudential's new "living needs benefit program," to be announced today, is the 
first mass market plan in the nation to allow life insurance policyholders 
access to their death benefits before they die. It will be available initially 
to policyholders in 10 states that have already approved the program. 
California is not among them. 
</P>
