<HEADLINE>
<P>
ORANGE COUNTY NEWSWATCH 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Mark I. Pinsky and Steve Emmons 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DERAILED: The weird vehicle you see humming along city streets this morning is 
exactly what it looks like: one of the original Disneyland monorail cars 
recently converted to a street machine. . . . Inside will be some Orange County 
mayors intent on seeing an 18-mile route proposed for a private 
Irvine-to-Anaheim monorail system. . . . Disney's "Mouseorail" soon heads out 
on a cross-country promotional tour. Mark I. Pinsky and Steve Emmons 
</P>
</TEXT>
<TYPE>
<P>
Column; Brief 
</P>
</TYPE>
<SUBJECT>
<P>
VEHICLES; ORANGE COUNTY -- GOVERNMENT OFFICIALS; ORANGE COUNTY -- 
TRANSPORTATION; PUBLIC RELATIONS; PUBLIC TRANSPORTATION; TRANSIT SYSTEMS -- 
ORANGE COUNTY 
</P>
</SUBJECT>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> LA012690-0104 </DOCNO>
<DOCID> 167434 </DOCID>
<DATE>
<P>
January 26, 1990, Friday, Orange County Edition 
</P>
</DATE>
<SECTION>
<P>
Part A; Page 1; Column 1; Metro Desk 
</P>
</SECTION>
<LENGTH>
<P>
104 words 
</P>
</LENGTH>
<HEADLINE>
<P>
ORANGE COUNTY NEWSWATCH 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Mark I. Pinsky and Steve Emmons 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
QUAYLE COUNTRY? Orange County adores conservatives but is oddly cool toward Dan 
Quayle, according to the Quayle Quarterly. . . . That's right: It's a new East 
Coast newsletter devoted entirely to the vice president. 
</P>
<P>
Issue No. 1 quotes local Republican campaign pros Eileen Padberg and Harvey 
Englander. "Orange County and Dan Quayle are both white bread. There should be 
a great fit there, but there isn't," Englander said. Padberg said local 
Republicans "are loyal, but not stupid. . . . Quayle may very well be qualified 
to be president in eight years, but he will have to prove it." Mark I. Pinsky 
and Steve Emmons 
</P>
</TEXT>
