<HEADLINE>
<P>
ORANGE COUNTY FOCUS: ANAHEIM; 
</P>
<P>
MEMBER SOUGHT FOR SENIORS COMMISSION 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The City Council is seeking individuals interested in filling a vacancy on the 
Senior Citizen Commission. 
</P>
<P>
Acting as an advisory board, the commission makes recommendations to the City 
Council regarding the needs and concerns of Anaheim's senior citizens. 
</P>
<P>
Members of the seven-person commission are appointed to a three-year term. 
Meetings are held the second Thursday of the month at 1:30 p.m. in the City 
Council chambers. 
</P>
<P>
Those applying must be at least 60 years old, not employed in city government 
and must be a qualified voter. People interested should submit a letter to the 
city clerk's office at 200 S. Anaheim Blvd., Anaheim, 92805. 
</P>
</TEXT>
