<HEADLINE>
<P>
SCHINTZIUS QUITS TEAM AT FLORIDA 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
GAINESVILLE, Fla. 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Dwayne Schintzius, Florida's leading scorer and rebounder until his suspension 
Jan. 15, said Thursday he is leaving the team because he doesn't want to "sail 
under the authority of Captain Ahab." 
</P>
<P>
The comment was an apparent reference to Coach Don DeVoe, who replaced Norm 
Sloan before the season. 
</P>
<P>
Schintzius and teammate Tim Turner had been suspended for their role in a fight 
at an off-campus fraternity. 
</P>
<P>
DeVoe said he invited Schintzius, a senior, back on the team Wednesday as long 
as Schintzius obeyed team policies. 
</P>
<P>
"No one can argue that Coach Sloan and (departed assistant coach Monte) Towe 
were easy to play for, and to them you had to accept the coach as the absolute 
authority," Schintzius said in a written statement. "But that does not mean you 
must sail under the authority of Captain Ahab. . . ." 
</P>
</TEXT>
<TYPE>
<P>
Wire 
</P>
</TYPE>
<SUBJECT>
<P>
BASKETBALL PLAYERS; UNIVERSITY OF FLORIDA; SCHINTZIUS, DWAYNE; SUSPENSIONS 
</P>
</SUBJECT>
