<HEADLINE>
<P>
SANTA MARGARITA BEATS VALLEY CHRISTIAN 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
RANCHO SANTA MARGARITA 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Sophomore guard Kristin Mulligan scored 15 of her game-high 26 points in the 
fourth quarter to lead Santa Margarita High School to a 44-41 victory over 
Valley Christian Thursday in an Olympic League girls' basketball game. 
</P>
<P>
Sarah Witte added 10 points for Santa Margarita (12-6 overall and 7-2 in league 
play). It was the first league defeat for first-place Valley Christian (8-1). 
</P>
<P>
Valley Christian led, 32-21, at the end of the third quarter, but Santa 
Margarita switched from a zone to a man-to-man defense to help the comeback. 
</P>
</TEXT>
