<HEADLINE>
<P>
TITAN BASEBALL TEAM LOSES PITCHER BAILEY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The Cal State Fullerton baseball team will be without pitcher Jack Bailey, who 
has been ruled academically ineligible, a school official said. 
</P>
<P>
Bailey, a transfer from Rancho Santiago College, was expected to be a starter 
for the Titans, who open their season Tuesday against Cal Poly Pomona at Titan 
Field. 
</P>
