4 KILLED IN ATTEMPT TO HIJACK IRAN AIR JET ON DOMESTIC FLIGHT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Wire Services 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
NICOSIA, Cyprus 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Security guards on a domestic Iran Air flight foiled a hijacking and killed all 
four hijackers in a shootout, IRNA news agency reported today. 
</P>
<P>
The agency, quoting a statement from the Islamic Revolutionary Guards, said 
four "armed terrorists" tried to hijack the Boeing 727 Thursday night on a 
flight between the southern cities of Shiraz and Bandar Abbas. 
</P>
<P>
The Islamic Revolutionary Guards, the internal security force, said all four 
hijackers were killed in a shoot-out with agents who were on the plane. 
</P>
<P>
The hijackers had taken a crew member hostage to force the pilot to fly to an 
unspecified destination. None of the passengers was wounded, and the plane 
returned to Shiraz after the attempt, IRNA said. 
</P>
