<HEADLINE>
<P>
THE SIDELINES; 
</P>
<P>
SOX' MARTINEZ JAILED IN ASSAULT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Wire Services 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
CHICAGO 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
White Sox infielder Carlos Martinez is in a Caracas, Venezuela, jail after his 
arrest on suspicion of hitting a man with a baseball bat, a newspaper reported 
today. 
</P>
<P>
A native Venezuelan in his second year with the Sox, Martinez was playing 
winter baseball for the LaGuaira Tiburones (Sharks), the newspaper said. 
</P>
<P>
Martinez allegedly went to University Stadium in Caracas with friends and 
relatives last Saturday to watch a baseball game. He got into trouble when he 
tried to get in without paying, the report said. 
</P>
<P>
Martinez allegedly argued with Homero Herrera, a stadium guard, who then picked 
up a baseball bat and tried to strike Martinez. Martinez than allegedly grabbed 
the bat and struck Herrera on the arm, the newspaper said. 
</P>
<P>
Venezuela does not have a bail system, and no decision has been made on whether 
Martinez will be given a trial. Sources said he would probably serve an 
eight-day sentence, the Tribune reported. 
</P>
</TEXT>
