<DATE>
<P>
January 26, 1990, Friday, Orange County Edition 
</P>
</DATE>
<SECTION>
<P>
Orange County Life; Part N; Page 2; Column 2 
</P>
</SECTION>
<LENGTH>
<P>
342 words 
</P>
</LENGTH>
<HEADLINE>
<P>
PRESIDENT'S DAY WEEKENDERS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Clipboard researched by Elena Brunet and Janice L. Jones / Los Angeles 
Times; Graphics by Scott Brown and Doris Shields / Los Angeles Times 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
President's Day weekend is peak skiing time in the Western United States. 
Flights to such skiing meccas as Lake Tahoe, Jackson Hole, Powderhorn (via 
Grand Junction, Colo.) and Sun Valley (via Boise) require a change of planes. A 
direct flight to Denver gets a skier within reach of Aspen and Vail, a flight 
to Portland takes you to Mt. Hood or Timberline Lodge, Seattle is within reach 
of Crystal Mountain. The thrifty passenger can save, depending on the 
destination and whether the flight carries restrictions. 
</P>
<P>
The following chart shows round-trip air fares to Albuquerque, Boise, Denver, 
Grand Junction, Jackson Hole, Lake Tahoe, Las Vegas, Portland (Ore.), Salt Lake 
City, San Francisco and Seattle from John Wayne Airport. Fares are for 
departure on Friday, Feb. 16, and returning Monday, Feb. 19. Las Vegas and San 
Francisco, while not necessarily skiing destinations, hold other allures. 
</P>
<P>
Two quotes are listed for each destination. The first quote is the lowest fare 
available, with various restrictions; the second is for unrestricted coach. See 
notes below. 
</P>
